Alexandria Media Management Library
  by Andrew Kozak < andrewkozak.com >

0. SETUP

0.a. Use the schema in /database/schema.sql to create the MySQL database
0.b. Copy config.php.sample to config.php
     $ cp config.php.sample config.php
0.c. Open config.php and fill in environment details
0.d. Chmod the TimThumb extension's /cache directory 
     $ chmod -R 777 third-party/timthumb/cache
0.e. Until a better solution is determined, chmod the following:
     $ chmod -R 777 stacks
     $ chmod -R 777 inbox

~!~ WARNINGS ~!~

re-chmod /inbox before each process session.
